# shadcn UI

This project uses **shadcn UI** for all UI elements. Use shadcn components only; do not introduce other UI libraries for buttons, forms, dialogs, etc.

## Initialization

If shadcn UI is not yet initialized in the project, run:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest init
```

- Always ask to user to run the commands.
- Preference prompts (style, base color, etc.) will be shown in the agent terminal; answer them as appropriate for the project.

## Adding components

If a specific component is missing, add it with:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add <component>
```

Examples:

- Button: `npx shadcn@latest add button`
- Card: `npx shadcn@latest add card`
- Dialog: `npx shadcn@latest add dialog`
- Input: `npx shadcn@latest add input`

Check the [shadcn UI docs](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components) for the exact component name when adding.

## Summary

- **All UI**: Use shadcn UI components.
- **Not initialized**: `npx shadcn@latest init` (answer prompts in terminal).
- **Component missing**: `npx shadcn@latest add <component>`.
